    "buildCommand": "cd /Users/mac/cat/catwallet-ops-backend\ngit push origin feature/i18n-upload-app-tab 2>&1 | grep -iE \"branch|github|pull|remote:\" | head -6\ngh pr create --base main --head feature/i18n-upload-app-tab \\\n  --title \"refactor(admin-web): move app upload to its own i18n tab\" \\\n  --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\nFollow-up to #15. Per feedback, the app-package upload belongs in its own tab in the i18n page, not as a button in the translations toolbar.\n\n## Changes\n- Remove the **Upload App Package** button from the translations toolbar.\n- Add a third tab **Upload App Package** to the i18n page, rendered only when the user holds `i18n:upload_app` (superadmin bypasses). Uses a drag-and-drop `Upload.Dragger` with a `Spin` overlay during upload.\n- Upload behavior unchanged: posts to `POST /i18n/uploadApp`, records an `upload_app` op-log, 130s client timeout.\n- Add `i18n.tab.uploadApp`, `i18n.uploadAppHint`, `i18n.uploadAppUploading` locale strings (zh/en); repurpose `i18n.uploadApp` as the dragger prompt text.\n\n## Testing\n- `tsc -p apps/admin-web --noEmit` clean\n- `npm run build` (admin-web) succeeds\n- Locale JSON validated\n\n## Deploy\nFrontend-only. Rebuild + redeploy admin-web: `docker compose build --no-cache admin-web && docker compose up -d admin-web`, then hard-refresh the browser.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1 | tail -3",
    "testCommand": "npx jest auth i18n 2>&1 | tail -30",
